<p><strong>Exploring the Historical Epic: The Physician by Noah Gordon</strong></p>
<p><strong>1. Who wrote The Physician?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The Physician is a historical novel written by American author Noah Gordon. It was first published in 1986.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>2. What is the main plot of the novel?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The Physician follows the journey of young Rob Cole, an 11th-century English barber-surgeon who travels to Persia in search of knowledge from the legendary physician Avicenna. Along the way, he encounters various obstacles, including religious and cultural differences, as well as the challenges of practicing medicine in a different era.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>3. Why is Avicenna considered a legendary physician?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Avicenna, known as Ibn Sina in Arabic, was a Persian polymath who lived in the 10th and 11th centuries. He is regarded as one of the most influential physicians in history. His textbook, The Canon of Medicine, was a comprehensive medical encyclopedia that was widely used for centuries.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>4. What is the significance of the setting in The Physician?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The novel is set in the 11th century, a time of great cultural and intellectual exchange between Europe and the Islamic world. This setting allows Gordon to explore the different medical practices and philosophies of the time.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>5. Where can you find a PDF version of The Physician?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The Physician by Noah Gordon is available as a PDF file from various sources, including online libraries and booksellers. You can search for "The Physician Noah Gordon PDF" to find a free or paid version of the book.</li>
</ul>